AI-Assisted Runtime Resource Optimization for Medical Devices

1. Invention Title

AI-Assisted Runtime Resource Optimization for Medical Devices

⸻

2. Detailed Description Of The Invention

Problem:

Modern medical devices utilize embedded software platforms running continuously for extended operational periods. Over time, subsystem performance degradation may occur due to memory leaks, CPU spikes, thread starvation, cache inefficiencies, communication bottlenecks, resource contention, and long-duration runtime instability.

Existing systems primarily rely on reactive diagnostics and post-failure troubleshooting mechanisms that identify issues only after visible operational degradation or subsystem malfunction occurs.

Current approaches generally do not provide intelligent runtime analysis capable of detecting gradual performance degradation trends or predicting future operational instability.

Solution:

The invention introduces an AI-assisted runtime resource optimization framework for embedded medical devices capable of continuously monitoring operational software metrics, identifying abnormal runtime behavior, predicting performance degradation trends, and generating preventive optimization recommendations.

The framework continuously monitors:

* CPU utilization
* Memory utilization
* Thread behavior
* Process latency
* Resource contention
* Cache usage
* Thermal conditions
* Communication latency
* Service health metrics

The invention includes:

* Runtime monitoring engine
* Embedded telemetry collection layer
* AI-assisted anomaly detection engine
* Resource optimization recommendation engine
* Runtime health scoring engine
* Service diagnostics framework

The monitoring engine continuously collects operational metrics from embedded applications and system services. The collected metrics are analyzed using rule-based logic and AI-assisted trend analysis techniques to identify abnormal resource utilization patterns and progressive runtime degradation.

The system generates optimization recommendations before visible operational instability occurs.

Example:
A display-rendering service exhibiting progressive memory growth, increased CPU usage, and response latency drift may indicate a memory leak or resource instability condition. The framework identifies the abnormal trend and generates a preventive optimization recommendation before application failure or system slowdown occurs.

The invention is intended as a non-clinical advisory runtime optimization framework and does not directly modify therapy delivery or patient-critical functionality.

